1
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:05,710
[Episode 7] [Torn Tenderness]

2
00:00:14,910 --> 00:00:15,880
Weren't we skipping class today?

3
00:00:15,880 --> 00:00:16,950
Where were you?

4
00:00:17,780 --> 00:00:18,850
Where's the sea turtle drawing?

5
00:00:18,850 --> 00:00:19,610
In my bag.

6
00:00:19,690 --> 00:00:20,560
Can I have it?

7
00:00:21,450 --> 00:00:22,450
What are you up to?

8
00:00:22,530 --> 00:00:23,850
Where exactly were you today?

9
00:00:23,850 --> 00:00:25,910
I've been waiting for you for so long.

10
00:00:28,020 --> 00:00:29,750
What on earth are you thinking?

11
00:00:31,090 --> 00:00:32,150
What are you doing?

12
00:00:32,530 --> 00:00:33,460
What are you doing?

13
00:00:33,460 --> 00:00:34,520
What are you doing?

14
00:00:35,230 --> 00:00:36,400
What are you doing?

15
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,060
What's wrong with you?

16
00:00:43,610 --> 00:00:44,910
What are you doing?

17
00:00:45,970 --> 00:00:47,100
I heard everything.

18
00:00:47,540 --> 00:00:48,780
What did you hear?

19
00:00:49,910 --> 00:00:51,570
I'm a terrible person anyway.

20
00:00:52,130 --> 00:00:54,600
I'm just a country bumpkin you despise.

21
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:57,920
No matter what we do,

22
00:00:58,660 --> 00:01:00,130
we always get judged

23
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:02,720
and end up being unwelcome.

24
00:01:03,380 --> 00:01:04,849
But I've tried my best.

25
00:01:06,490 --> 00:01:08,160
But I failed every time.

26
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,460
Unlike you,

27
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:11,030
everything you do

28
00:01:11,330 --> 00:01:12,530
gets praised.

29
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,640
Everyone always says you're amazing.

30
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:15,900
You won't feel lonely.

31
00:01:18,310 --> 00:01:19,470
But I'm different.

32
00:01:20,780 --> 00:01:22,880
I grew up on an island.

33
00:01:24,550 --> 00:01:26,550
I don't have time to study.

34
00:01:29,350 --> 00:01:31,250
And no one wants to be my friend.

35
00:01:31,990 --> 00:01:33,890
That's why I draw alone.

36
00:01:34,910 --> 00:01:36,600
Thank you for accepting
such a lousy gift from me.

37
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:37,340
I...

38
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:39,789
She and I were just...

39
00:01:39,789 --> 00:01:40,460
just...

40
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:41,630
I just went along with what she said.

41
00:01:41,630 --> 00:01:42,759
I was only trying to brush her off.

42
00:01:42,759 --> 00:01:44,620
-Brush her off?
-I really didn't—

43
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:46,130
So you always treat your friends this way,

44
00:01:46,130 --> 00:01:47,670
just half-heartedly?

45
00:01:47,670 --> 00:01:49,650
She and I are not friends at all!

46
00:01:51,070 --> 00:01:52,770
How can I believe you?

47
00:01:53,170 --> 00:01:53,910
Did you say that because you

48
00:01:53,910 --> 00:01:55,050
don't want to end this relationship?

49
00:01:55,050 --> 00:01:57,120
Or are you just brushing me off?

50
00:01:57,810 --> 00:01:59,680
There's really nothing between her and me.

51
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,760
Chen Haowei.

52
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:04,500
Thank you for giving me
such a wonderful dream.

53
00:02:05,150 --> 00:02:05,990
What do you mean?

54
00:02:05,990 --> 00:02:07,760
Now that I've woken up from my dream,

55
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,759
I should leave.

56
00:02:08,910 --> 00:02:09,830
What do you mean?

57
00:02:09,830 --> 00:02:11,090
Don't come to me again.

58
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:12,020
What are you talking about?

59
00:02:12,020 --> 00:02:14,080
Just act like I were never here, okay?

60
00:02:14,470 --> 00:02:15,310
He Xiangyong.

61
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:17,970
We're not from the same world at all.

62
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,800
I don't understand.

63
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:22,270
You can keep smiling later.

64
00:02:22,670 --> 00:02:23,840
Without me,

65
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:25,810
you can smile more happily anyway.

66
00:02:25,810 --> 00:02:27,610
What are you talking about, He Xiangyong?

67
00:02:27,610 --> 00:02:28,410
He Xiangyong!

68
00:02:40,650 --> 00:02:42,450
What the hell?

69
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:47,400
He Xiangyong!

70
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:50,870
He Xiangyong!

71
00:02:53,650 --> 00:02:55,210
He Xiangyong!

72
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,340
He Xiangyong!

73
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:05,040
He Xiangyong!

74
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:02,430
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

75
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:09,140
Mr. He.

76
00:04:09,830 --> 00:04:11,000
Let's have a drink.

77
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:11,990
Sure.

78
00:04:12,010 --> 00:04:13,210
Come on, have a drink.

79
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:16,610
Come on.

80
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:18,320
Drink.

81
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:29,990
I've decided to go back
to the main island.

82
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,200
Are you quitting?

83
00:04:34,330 --> 00:04:36,260
Why are you leaving all of a sudden?

84
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:43,680
Actually,

85
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,600
my vacation is over.

86
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:49,140
The company has been urging
me to go back to work.

87
00:04:49,950 --> 00:04:51,550
I can't delay it any further.

88
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,560
Mr. He.

89
00:04:55,210 --> 00:04:56,280
I'm sorry.

90
00:04:56,310 --> 00:04:57,870
I decided without asking you.

91
00:04:57,870 --> 00:04:59,790
What are you sorry for?

92
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,880
You helped me a lot.

93
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:07,500
Besides, after everything that's happened
at the guesthouse lately,

94
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:10,960
I figure you wouldn't feel comfortable
bringing it up anyway.

95
00:05:12,770 --> 00:05:14,040
Just go back.

96
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:16,650
This is just a place
where you young people

97
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:19,030
catch your breath and rest for a while.

98
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:21,320
Go back and work hard.

99
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:24,690
Remember to come back when you're tired.

100
00:05:24,690 --> 00:05:26,820
Hua, Angela,

101
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:27,660
and I

102
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:29,140
will be here to back you up.

103
00:05:29,870 --> 00:05:30,460
Okay.

104
00:05:32,460 --> 00:05:33,460
Thank you, Mr. He.

105
00:05:38,980 --> 00:05:39,909
What about me?

106
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,240
Do you have something to tell me?

107
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:49,500
You...

108
00:05:50,659 --> 00:05:52,790
just take good care of the guesthouse.

109
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:01,460
What is it? Come on.

110
00:06:01,460 --> 00:06:02,190
Raise your glass.

111
00:06:02,190 --> 00:06:03,920
Let's drink together, come on.

112
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,220
You guys drink.

113
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:06,450
I don't want to drink.

114
00:06:06,490 --> 00:06:07,230
Don't drink if you don't want to.

115
00:06:07,230 --> 00:06:07,960
Come on, let's drink.

116
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:08,960
Thank you, Mr. He.

117
00:06:20,780 --> 00:06:22,460
Thank you.

118
00:06:21,810 --> 00:06:34,710
[Stairway Corner Ice]

119
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:42,060
Li Wanzhe,

120
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:44,130
do you really think you are
some young master of the Li family,

121
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:44,830
don't you?

122
00:06:44,830 --> 00:06:46,800
Why did you dump
all your work on Hama-chan?

123
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,870
I didn't.

124
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:49,090
I'm working now.

125
00:06:49,110 --> 00:06:50,040
Counting the money.

126
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,500
Keeping an eye on the work.

127
00:06:51,670 --> 00:06:53,700
Auntie, stop scolding him.

128
00:06:53,730 --> 00:06:55,270
I told him to rest.

129
00:06:57,310 --> 00:06:59,580
I haven't started yet.

130
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,880
Why are you laughing?

131
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,870
How can you dump
all your work on someone else

132
00:07:08,890 --> 00:07:10,330
and not even feel guilty?

133
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:11,400
Why should I?

134
00:07:11,420 --> 00:07:13,260
Hama-chan told me to rest.

135
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,890
Weird.

136
00:07:17,570 --> 00:07:19,700
Hama-chan can get pretty good pay

137
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:21,660
and benefits sailing with Zhong.

138
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,310
Why would he give up?

139
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,670
Maybe Hama-chan came here

140
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:27,930
just because he thinks
our family offers better benefits.

141
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:31,810
You mean you?

142
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:37,830
Is he out of it?

143
00:07:38,550 --> 00:07:38,990
Forget it.

144
00:07:38,990 --> 00:07:40,720
I'm done caring about you guys.

145
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:42,560
We made good money today.

146
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:44,030
Yes, it's exactly 8,700,

147
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:45,260
not one cent short.

148
00:07:49,650 --> 00:07:51,510
Hide it somewhere else next time.

149
00:07:52,230 --> 00:07:52,830
All right.

150
00:07:52,830 --> 00:07:55,870
I'm off to enjoy some grown-up nightlife.

151
00:07:58,300 --> 00:07:59,140
Wait, Mom,

152
00:07:59,159 --> 00:08:00,960
you've only left me some change?

153
00:08:02,410 --> 00:08:04,180
Li Wanzhe, are you hungry?

154
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:08,350
You've been working hard all day.

155
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:10,580
Let me make you some late-night snacks.

156
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:13,590
Okay.

157
00:08:13,610 --> 00:08:14,270
Good.

158
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:16,520
I'll get the dishes done quickly.

159
00:08:20,030 --> 00:08:23,360
Does it really have something
to do with the shooting stars?

160
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,690
Why do you have the sea turtle drawing?

161
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,120
Didn't you tear it apart back then?

162
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,480
Why did you put it back together?

163
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:19,470
Why have you kept it for so long?

164
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:23,450
What do you mean
by asking me to hand it over to him?

165
00:09:26,730 --> 00:09:28,390
He must be really close to you.

166
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:32,230
He even told you
about the sea turtle drawing.

167
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,110
I thought...

168
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:43,480
it was just a story between us.

169
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:47,980
Between you two?

170
00:09:50,170 --> 00:09:51,770
Between you and them, right?

171
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:56,950
Didn't you laugh at him
together with everyone else?

172
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:00,390
Do you know how painful it was

173
00:10:00,390 --> 00:10:01,920
for him to hear those words?

174
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:09,930
It was not like that.

175
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:14,150
Back then...

176
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:20,550
I cared too much
about everyone's thoughts,

177
00:10:20,550 --> 00:10:22,810
and I wanted to please everyone too much.

178
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:25,440
For the past 10 years,

179
00:10:26,070 --> 00:10:28,130
I have regretted it every single day.

180
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:31,380
I really want to apologize to him.

181
00:10:46,370 --> 00:10:47,940
If you regret it,

182
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:52,240
why come looking for him only now?

183
00:10:54,050 --> 00:10:55,650
I'm afraid that if I go to him,

184
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,450
I'll only make him resent me.

185
00:11:00,220 --> 00:11:01,750
It seems that Xingpu Island

186
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:04,360
is still on his side.

187
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,730
He came back before,

188
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:12,820
but we still ended up missing each other.

189
00:11:17,540 --> 00:11:18,540
Well...

190
00:11:20,210 --> 00:11:22,010
Do you have anything to tell him?

191
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:27,370
I can tell him for you.

192
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:38,850
He said that here was the paradise
of sea turtles.

193
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:45,490
I fixed the sea turtle drawing,

194
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,120
hoping to heal his broken heart.

195
00:11:53,310 --> 00:11:55,120
I hope he can find his paradise.

196
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:06,290
I don't expect him to forgive me.

197
00:12:10,930 --> 00:12:13,260
I just want him to be happy every day.

198
00:12:25,940 --> 00:12:28,580
He's always the best painter

199
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:32,300
and the best He Xiangyong in my heart.

200
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:54,970
I believe he will forgive you

201
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,000
after hearing what you said.

202
00:13:01,340 --> 00:13:02,380
Though his life

203
00:13:02,810 --> 00:13:04,680
is often far from perfect,

204
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:07,650
I think

205
00:13:07,850 --> 00:13:09,650
at the very least, in your heart,

206
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:13,950
he still ranks among the best.

207
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:16,980
Sometimes,

208
00:13:20,130 --> 00:13:22,660
I really think
you're a lot like He Xiangyong.

209
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,750
Chen Haowei,

210
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:44,890
how long on earth

211
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:46,490
have you spent on this?

212
00:13:57,150 --> 00:13:58,320
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

213
00:14:04,990 --> 00:14:06,420
Your Haowei

214
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:08,380
is going back to work on the main island.

215
00:14:08,380 --> 00:14:09,410
In that case,

216
00:14:09,410 --> 00:14:11,920
we'll lose a young man to help us.

217
00:14:13,710 --> 00:14:15,010
Hang in there.

218
00:14:15,970 --> 00:14:18,010
My pension is all on you.

219
00:14:18,030 --> 00:14:20,000
The guesthouse can't go under.

220
00:14:21,190 --> 00:14:22,390
I used to work alone,

221
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:24,250
and did it ever go under back then?

222
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:26,920
I bought this place.

223
00:14:27,430 --> 00:14:29,500
Are you here to fight or drink?

224
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:30,600
Alright.

225
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:31,770
Stop nagging.

226
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:34,510
Have you ever thought
of asking Xiangyong for help?

227
00:14:34,510 --> 00:14:35,210
Of course.

228
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:36,790
I don't even know where he is now.

229
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:37,530
Forget it.

230
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:40,140
He'll come back when he figures it out.

231
00:14:40,510 --> 00:14:41,480
Let me tell you,

232
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:44,210
you just spoil your son too much.

233
00:14:44,450 --> 00:14:46,250
If my son dares to do such a thing,

234
00:14:46,290 --> 00:14:46,990
please,

235
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:49,520
call 113 (domestic violence
and child protection hotline) for him,

236
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:50,700
okay? To save him.

237
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,320
I'm not spoiling him.

238
00:14:55,390 --> 00:14:57,160
I know him well.

239
00:14:58,090 --> 00:15:00,790
He's never liked being forced
to do things since he was a kid.

240
00:15:00,790 --> 00:15:01,960
He's just like

241
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:03,300
a rubber ball you push underwater.

242
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:06,500
The harder you press him down,
the higher he bounces back.

243
00:15:07,130 --> 00:15:08,000
Really?

244
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,040
Of course.

245
00:15:09,350 --> 00:15:10,700
Once I caught him drawing secretly,

246
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:12,370
I confiscated all his painting supplies.

247
00:15:12,370 --> 00:15:13,580
So he picked up stones

248
00:15:13,770 --> 00:15:15,040
and drew a whole zoo

249
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,640
right under this very chair
you're sitting on.

250
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:17,970
Look how amazing he was.

251
00:15:34,210 --> 00:15:35,360
Why don't I remember it?

252
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,530
Did it happen after I came here?

253
00:15:37,830 --> 00:15:40,060
Are you so old
that you can't remember anything?

254
00:15:40,060 --> 00:15:41,820
That one time
he had a fever of 40 degrees,

255
00:15:41,820 --> 00:15:43,280
he hid under the quilt,
secretly drawing anyway.

256
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:45,410
I got so mad that I took away
all his art supplies in one go.

257
00:15:45,410 --> 00:15:47,930
Don't you remember?
You were right beside me.

258
00:15:47,930 --> 00:15:49,260
Did that really happen?

259
00:15:50,860 --> 00:15:51,960
See for yourself.

260
00:15:52,450 --> 00:15:53,450
Have a look.

261
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:55,780
Where is it?

262
00:15:55,810 --> 00:15:57,040
Nothing.

263
00:15:59,000 --> 00:15:59,630
Nothing.

264
00:15:59,650 --> 00:16:00,950
This is bad.

265
00:16:01,590 --> 00:16:04,160
You really should eat more ginkgo nuts

266
00:16:04,190 --> 00:16:06,660
or take fish oil and the like,
don't you think?

267
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:08,060
Could it be that Sister-in-Law

268
00:16:08,060 --> 00:16:09,560
replaced the whole table
and chairs entirely

269
00:16:09,560 --> 00:16:11,490
and you've forgotten it yourself?

270
00:16:13,530 --> 00:16:14,730
How is that possible?

271
00:16:17,330 --> 00:16:18,500
Come on. Drink.

272
00:16:18,530 --> 00:16:20,590
You're just getting on in years.

273
00:17:10,530 --> 00:17:11,430
I think

274
00:17:11,460 --> 00:17:13,800
we work really well together as a team.

275
00:17:15,170 --> 00:17:16,430
After you leave,

276
00:17:16,460 --> 00:17:18,060
Mr. He will think I'm clumsy.

277
00:17:21,319 --> 00:17:22,150
No way.

278
00:17:23,190 --> 00:17:25,250
Your garlic shrimp vermicelli
is so delicious,

279
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:25,940
right?

280
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:27,420
Mr. He likes it so much.

281
00:17:30,140 --> 00:17:31,340
What about Uncle Hua?

282
00:17:31,930 --> 00:17:33,660
You always go fishing with him.

283
00:17:33,670 --> 00:17:34,540
Without you,

284
00:17:34,570 --> 00:17:36,170
he must feel lonely.

285
00:17:39,090 --> 00:17:40,350
With Mr. He

286
00:17:40,690 --> 00:17:42,020
and Angela here,

287
00:17:42,050 --> 00:17:43,690
how would he feel lonely?

288
00:17:46,060 --> 00:17:46,790
Yeah.

289
00:17:47,130 --> 00:17:48,400
Speaking of Angela,

290
00:17:48,810 --> 00:17:50,110
she always said

291
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:52,280
that as long as you drop by their shop,

292
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:53,550
business will pick up.

293
00:17:56,870 --> 00:17:57,470
That's because

294
00:17:57,470 --> 00:17:58,840
their shaved ice is always delicious,

295
00:17:58,840 --> 00:17:59,570
okay?

296
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:04,580
Well,

297
00:18:05,450 --> 00:18:07,080
after you leave,

298
00:18:08,050 --> 00:18:09,850
I'll be alone at the guesthouse.

299
00:18:10,180 --> 00:18:14,380
I'll have to do the work of two people
all by myself, and it'll be exhausting.

300
00:18:16,060 --> 00:18:17,660
The peak season has passed.

301
00:18:17,970 --> 00:18:20,570
Things will ease up
once the off-season comes.

302
00:18:23,090 --> 00:18:24,950
Why do you leave everything to me?

303
00:18:25,550 --> 00:18:26,450
I don't.

304
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:39,640
Shall we

305
00:18:40,170 --> 00:18:41,980
play the game we used to play?

306
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,250
We ask each other a question

307
00:18:44,580 --> 00:18:46,380
and answer each other honestly.

308
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:58,900
How do you feel

309
00:18:59,390 --> 00:19:00,790
about me?

310
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,510
I feel...

311
00:19:11,110 --> 00:19:13,110
I feel you need to be more confident.

312
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:15,760
You are so nice,

313
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:16,660
right?

314
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,270
You can do your work well later.

315
00:19:39,730 --> 00:19:40,330
Well,

316
00:19:40,550 --> 00:19:41,750
it's your turn to ask.

317
00:19:43,940 --> 00:19:46,540
I'll ask you
when I've figured out my question.

318
00:19:58,580 --> 00:20:00,270
[Orion 2026 Asia Tour]
[Venue: Weiwuying, Kaohsiung]

319
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:07,620
[Too many users online.
Please wait and retry.]

320
00:20:11,910 --> 00:20:12,980
Li Wanzhe!

321
00:20:13,010 --> 00:20:13,940
What?

322
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:16,180
Your mom asked you to come down and help!

323
00:20:16,180 --> 00:20:18,380
We've got so many customers today,
and we can't keep up!

324
00:20:18,380 --> 00:20:20,240
Wait a minute! I'm busy right now!

325
00:20:25,050 --> 00:20:26,310
What are you busy with?

326
00:20:26,390 --> 00:20:28,990
Don't disturb me.
I'm trying to get the ticket.

327
00:20:32,430 --> 00:20:33,690
I can't get in.

328
00:20:35,130 --> 00:20:36,360
How is that possible?

329
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:42,540
I knew it.

330
00:20:42,940 --> 00:20:44,840
I've never gotten a ticket.

331
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:47,240
You want to go to the concert?

332
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:48,140
Yes.

333
00:20:48,340 --> 00:20:50,270
It's been 10 years
since he last held a concert here.

334
00:20:50,270 --> 00:20:52,600
Who knows when he'll come again next time.

335
00:20:53,410 --> 00:20:55,810
How about buying a scalper ticket instead?

336
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:58,380
I don't want to buy a scalper ticket.

337
00:20:58,490 --> 00:20:59,520
That's exactly

338
00:20:59,520 --> 00:21:00,690
why I can't get a ticket—

339
00:21:00,690 --> 00:21:02,000
scalpers bought them all up.

340
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,730
There's no way I'm letting them
make money off me.

341
00:21:05,660 --> 00:21:06,360
Forget it.

342
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:08,600
I'm not a big fan anyway.

343
00:21:09,410 --> 00:21:11,630
Just hang out and play games
with me for a few days,

344
00:21:11,630 --> 00:21:13,620
and let me forget all about this.

345
00:21:28,950 --> 00:21:30,050
If you want to come,

346
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:31,510
take a boat.

347
00:21:32,210 --> 00:21:33,410
The island is a small place.

348
00:21:33,410 --> 00:21:34,710
You won't get lost.

349
00:21:37,610 --> 00:21:40,030
When you get off the boat,
turn left and go straight,

350
00:21:40,030 --> 00:21:41,760
and you'll see a grocery store.

351
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,040
In my childhood,

352
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,420
when I went to buy watermelon candy,

353
00:21:44,420 --> 00:21:46,280
the shop owner would give me more.

354
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:49,040
His daughter and he bickered all the time.

355
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,700
It was just their daily thing.

356
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,630
Sleeping day and night.

357
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:54,410
-You old man.
-You really...

358
00:21:54,410 --> 00:21:56,460
How am I supposed
to write songs like this?

359
00:21:56,460 --> 00:21:57,400
Sir.

360
00:21:58,300 --> 00:21:59,220
How much is the candy?

361
00:21:59,220 --> 00:21:59,850
This one?

362
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:00,920
Well,

363
00:22:00,940 --> 00:22:02,310
pick one yourself.

364
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:03,050
Okay.

365
00:22:03,050 --> 00:22:04,530
Is this your first time here?

366
00:22:04,530 --> 00:22:05,500
Yes, it's my first time here.

367
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:07,130
Eleven for the price of 10.

368
00:22:10,110 --> 00:22:11,180
Wanzhe's house

369
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:14,260
is at the corner of the shopping street
across the pier.

370
00:22:14,300 --> 00:22:15,770
His mother is Angela.

371
00:22:16,180 --> 00:22:16,860
You'd better

372
00:22:16,860 --> 00:22:18,520
avoid making her sound older.

373
00:22:24,150 --> 00:22:25,210
Walk all the way to the end,

374
00:22:25,210 --> 00:22:28,210
and you'll find a hidden paradise
known only to locals.

375
00:22:28,210 --> 00:22:30,410
It's also a secret base of Wanzhe and me.

376
00:22:30,740 --> 00:22:32,650
We call it Haitai,

377
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:34,790
because it's covered

378
00:22:34,810 --> 00:22:36,370
in lots of moss and seaweed.

379
00:22:37,020 --> 00:22:38,450
As long as we are stressed out

380
00:22:38,450 --> 00:22:39,450
and want to relax,

381
00:22:39,450 --> 00:22:40,620
we come here.

382
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:00,390
You rattle these numbers off
with your eyes closed:

383
00:23:00,390 --> 00:23:02,760
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

384
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:08,780
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

385
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:13,460
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

386
00:23:22,090 --> 00:23:24,090
Ride along the coast for 10 minutes,

387
00:23:24,260 --> 00:23:26,030
and you'll see an old building.

388
00:23:26,700 --> 00:23:28,160
There's a sign at the door,

389
00:23:28,250 --> 00:23:29,520
saying "Home at He's."

390
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:33,340
The name was chosen on purpose,

391
00:23:33,590 --> 00:23:35,340
so that no matter where guests come from

392
00:23:35,340 --> 00:23:37,190
or why they're here,

393
00:23:37,740 --> 00:23:39,360
they'll feel right at home—

394
00:23:39,770 --> 00:23:43,240
just like they've never been away at all.

395
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:55,100
Why did you draw
so many sea turtles on the paper?

396
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:56,330
I feel so happy

397
00:23:56,330 --> 00:23:57,790
when drawing sea turtles.

398
00:24:15,980 --> 00:24:17,080
Excuse me.

399
00:24:18,020 --> 00:24:19,590
Anyone here?

400
00:24:40,410 --> 00:24:41,510
Hello.

401
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:43,460
Welcome.

402
00:24:43,950 --> 00:24:45,180
So pretty here.

403
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:46,630
Let us know if you need a guide.

404
00:24:46,630 --> 00:24:47,330
Come here.

405
00:24:47,350 --> 00:24:48,820
What took you so long to buy groceries?

406
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:51,620
Come quickly
and help me type this on the computer.

407
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:52,890
What's wrong?

408
00:24:53,650 --> 00:24:54,520
It's just you here today,

409
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:56,720
and we've got quite a lot to get through.

410
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:58,650
What do you mean?

411
00:25:00,330 --> 00:25:01,530
Has Chen Haowei left?

412
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:02,860
Didn't he tell you?

413
00:25:03,660 --> 00:25:04,970
I think he left something for you.

414
00:25:04,970 --> 00:25:05,790
Take a look.

415
00:25:13,490 --> 00:25:14,560
Thank you.

416
00:25:15,390 --> 00:25:16,130
Take care.

417
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:20,410
If you want to go see him off,

418
00:25:20,410 --> 00:25:22,210
you can still make it to the pier.

419
00:25:25,330 --> 00:25:26,860
I'll help you with it later.

420
00:26:05,180 --> 00:26:06,910
Just one ticket. Thank you.

421
00:26:09,650 --> 00:26:10,890
Chen Haowei.

422
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:12,800
Give me 5 minutes.

423
00:26:14,750 --> 00:26:16,280
Let me buy the ticket first.

424
00:26:16,380 --> 00:26:17,050
Wait.

425
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:18,660
Sorry for the trouble, Miss.

426
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:20,060
He'll buy a ticket later.

427
00:26:20,740 --> 00:26:21,940
Just 5 minutes.

428
00:26:22,890 --> 00:26:23,630
Please.

429
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:30,770
Just say it if you have anything to say.

430
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:36,020
Can you

431
00:26:36,750 --> 00:26:37,870
stay?

432
00:26:44,230 --> 00:26:46,090
I can't put off my work any longer.

433
00:26:50,470 --> 00:26:52,040
What if I tell you

434
00:26:52,370 --> 00:26:53,370
that I like you?

435
00:26:59,380 --> 00:27:00,910
I only treat you as a friend.

436
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:06,520
If you only see me as a friend,

437
00:27:07,110 --> 00:27:09,840
why did you kiss me
when you were drunk that night?

438
00:27:13,270 --> 00:27:14,710
I didn't want to hurt you.

439
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:18,630
So you didn't even say goodbye?

440
00:27:21,470 --> 00:27:23,330
You missed that person back then.

441
00:27:23,690 --> 00:27:26,090
Are you gonna give up on me
this time as well?

442
00:27:30,380 --> 00:27:31,340
Are you done?

443
00:27:35,450 --> 00:27:36,220
Chen Haowei.

444
00:27:39,140 --> 00:27:40,110
Answer me.

445
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:51,360
The person I can't let go of
is He Xiangyong.

446
00:27:53,100 --> 00:27:55,600
The person I've always loved
is also He Xiangyong.

447
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:56,660
Do you understand?

448
00:27:58,910 --> 00:28:00,810
I see so much of him in you.

449
00:28:03,410 --> 00:28:06,270
It just makes me realize
I've never gotten over him.

450
00:28:08,350 --> 00:28:09,520
I mistook you for him

451
00:28:09,540 --> 00:28:11,140
and fell for you for a moment.

452
00:28:11,320 --> 00:28:13,380
Even so, do you really not care at all?

453
00:28:16,180 --> 00:28:17,080
It's okay.

454
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,400
You can continue to like him.

455
00:28:23,060 --> 00:28:24,860
You can think of me as him.

456
00:28:32,100 --> 00:28:32,830
Chen Haowei.

457
00:28:33,270 --> 00:28:34,000
Chen Haowei.

458
00:28:34,260 --> 00:28:35,330
I am him!

459
00:28:35,710 --> 00:28:36,940
I've liked you for 10 years.

460
00:28:36,940 --> 00:28:38,880
I'm the one who has always liked you!

461
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:39,780
You were a big shot in school,

462
00:28:39,780 --> 00:28:40,650
and I was a nobody

463
00:28:40,650 --> 00:28:41,880
stuck at the bottom of the class rankings.

464
00:28:41,880 --> 00:28:42,620
We skipped class

465
00:28:42,620 --> 00:28:43,580
and got caught by the instructor.

466
00:28:43,580 --> 00:28:44,920
You tutored me in my studies,
and I taught you to paint.

467
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:46,450
And you even said
I got Takehiko Inoue's talent for drawing.

468
00:28:46,450 --> 00:28:47,250
I gave you that sea turtle drawing
on your birthday.

469
00:28:47,250 --> 00:28:48,110
That's enough!

470
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:51,530
Stop it!

471
00:28:55,730 --> 00:28:57,200
I know you're close to him.

472
00:28:58,090 --> 00:28:59,920
He shared everything with you.

473
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:05,600
But love just doesn't work that way.

474
00:29:06,230 --> 00:29:07,900
You have your own life to live,

475
00:29:10,980 --> 00:29:14,450
and there's no need for you
to become like He Xiangyong just for me.

476
00:29:14,450 --> 00:29:16,420
I hurt him before.

477
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:17,970
This time,

478
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,490
I don't want anyone to get hurt again.

479
00:29:19,490 --> 00:29:20,460
Chen Haowei.

480
00:29:20,750 --> 00:29:22,080
Chen Haowei, please don't leave.

481
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:23,000
-Please don't leave!
-Don't stop me!

482
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:23,900
Chen Haowei!

483
00:29:25,860 --> 00:29:28,260
You think I'm him too, don't you?

484
00:29:28,820 --> 00:29:30,680
Why don't you trust yourself,

485
00:29:30,710 --> 00:29:32,120
Chen Haowei?

486
00:29:38,170 --> 00:29:46,530
[Epilogue]

487
00:29:47,760 --> 00:29:49,930
You only slept for a few minutes
and already started drawing.

488
00:29:49,930 --> 00:29:51,740
Didn't I tell you to review your lessons?

489
00:29:51,740 --> 00:29:53,610
I'll do that later.

490
00:29:53,970 --> 00:29:55,170
What are you drawing?

491
00:29:55,490 --> 00:29:56,760
Wait!

492
00:29:57,290 --> 00:29:57,990
Wait!

493
00:30:01,060 --> 00:30:03,110
I've been practicing
portrait drawing lately.

494
00:30:03,110 --> 00:30:04,210
Portrait drawing, huh?

495
00:30:04,210 --> 00:30:04,970
Yes.

496
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:07,020
I'm leaving. Bye-bye.

497
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:08,320
He Xiangyong.

498
00:30:09,930 --> 00:30:11,330
Don't give up on drawing.

499
00:30:13,380 --> 00:30:15,410
Why are you bringing this up
all of a sudden?

500
00:30:15,410 --> 00:30:16,510
Because that

501
00:30:16,980 --> 00:30:18,580
is what you really like to do.

502
00:30:20,550 --> 00:30:21,880
I want to follow your art

503
00:30:22,180 --> 00:30:23,580
forever and always

504
00:30:24,120 --> 00:30:25,920
and be your biggest fan forever.

505
00:30:57,170 --> 00:31:02,870
[Next Episode]

506
00:30:57,250 --> 00:30:58,620
Because he wanted to steal my ticket.

507
00:30:58,620 --> 00:31:00,150
If I die like this,

508
00:31:00,150 --> 00:31:01,750
you'll remember me forever.

509
00:31:03,090 --> 00:31:04,890
If we're going to walk this path,

510
00:31:05,830 --> 00:31:07,430
let's walk it for a lifetime.

511
00:31:10,450 --> 00:31:12,390
Happiness gained from a wish…

512
00:31:14,190 --> 00:31:15,990
I wonder how long it will hold up.
